The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Cardiff to stage Ashes Test 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     CRICKET BRIEFS
                      
	Cardiff to stage Ashes Test  
	Calcutta: Cardiff will stage the first Test in next years Ashes series between England and Australia, the ECB announced on Friday. It will be the first Test ever played in the Welsh city.  
	The match at Sophia Gardens will start on Wednesday, July 8, rather than the traditional Thursday.         
	The ECB also said the Rose Bowl near Southampton was set to become Englands 10th Test match venue by staging a Test against Sri Lanka in 2011.         
	Schedule         
	The Ashes  First Test: Sophia Gardens, Cardiff, July 8-12; Second Test: Lords, July 16-20; Third Test: Edgbaston, July 30-Aug. 3; Fourth Test: Headingley, Aug. 7-11; Fifth Test: The Oval, Aug. 20-24.                 
	Gooch raps ECB  
	London: Criticising the ECB for preventing English players from featuring in the inaugural IPL, former captain Graham Gooch said the decision was not a long-term option. Accommodation will be made between our board and the players, Gooch said. Theres a lot of sabre rattling but it will all be sorted out in the end.    
	Preity Lee to sell tickets  
	Mohali: Kings XI Punjab will start its sale of tickets from Saturday at the PCA Stadium here for the IPL meet. Kings XI Punjab owner Preity Zinta and star player Brett Lee would be present at the stadium to personally sell and autograph the tickets being sold.     
	Felicitation  
	Calcutta: The ICC will felicitate Anil Kumble, Ricky Ponting and Graeme Smith for their standing in the ICC rankings. The felicitation will take place in Mumbai on Wednesday. The ICCs outgoing chief executive Malcolm Speed will also be present on the occasion.                                                                                                                        
